  "body": "*Description*:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/ed300943217723dbc449480afd3f967e08ac4c95/source/common/router/config_impl.cc#L667-L679\r\n\r\nAt present envoy uses the HTTP/2 pseudo header semantics internally, and the query segments are considered part of the `:path` header. That makes query string get stripped when performing [http path_redirect](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/api-v3/config/route/v3/route_components.proto#envoy-v3-api-field-config-route-v3-redirectaction-path-redirect) even if [`strip_query`](https://www.envoyproxy.io/docs/envoy/latest/api-v3/config/route/v3/route_components.proto#envoy-v3-api-field-config-route-v3-redirectaction-strip-query) is set to false.\r\n\r\nIs it feasible to leave the query string intact by default? If query string was kept by default and we want to strip it, we could just set `strip_query` to true. ",
